# Keep the OS map current

The `/dev/os-map` page (also `/dashboard`) is an interactive, Railway-style
canvas meant to be a true visual of the project's guts and workflow. When you
add, remove, or significantly change a feature, service, API route, external
integration, or Telegram bot command, update the map **in the same change**.

Single source of truth: **`public/dev/os-map-data.js`**

- `NODES` — services / integrations / clients (id, title, sub, icon, hue, status, ghost, group, x, y).
- `EDGES` — connections (from, to, label, dashed, ghost).
- `GROUPS` — Railway-project-style containers (id, title, hue, members).

Give each node a distinct `hue` (0–360) so the map stays full-spectrum. The
render/interaction engine is `public/dev/os-map-loader.js` (drag + snap, pan,
zoom, persistence) — only touch it for behavior changes, not content.
